    {
      "id": "6f0126b1_ecdae96f",
      "file_path": "cps-ncmp-service/src/main/java/org/onap/cps/ncmp/init/SubscriptionModelLoader.java",
      "patchset_number": 3,
      "line": 88,
      "message": "Please ignore my prev. comment. I have re-write that here:\n\nAt max retry, the current values will reach almost 200 seconds ~ 3.3 minutes too long. \n\nAlso, the other way suggested as attemptCount * 1000 will result in 210 seconds (1s+2s+3s...+20s= 210 seconds). Almost the same. I think still too long to wait.\n\nMaybe, Thread.sleep(5000) is much more better since it is 1.6 minutes max.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 8063,
        "name": "Halil Cakal",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "halil.cakal@est.tech",
        "username": "halil.cakal"
      },
      "updated": "2023-04-27 15:12:58.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "67683c94_4d4ed683",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "id": "9d45952b_c2625737",
      "file_path": "cps-ncmp-service/src/main/java/org/onap/cps/ncmp/init/SubscriptionModelLoader.java",
      "patchset_number": 9,
      "line": 94,
      "message": "This will cause 1s + 2s + 3s + .. = 20*21/2=210 second too long. As we discussed earlier in a daily at that day you was not there. Thus you might miss that. \n\nSo, you may do this line Thread.sleep(retryTimeMs)",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 8063,
        "name": "Halil Cakal",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "halil.cakal@est.tech",
        "username": "halil.cakal"
      },
      "updated": "2023-04-27 15:12:58.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": null,
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
